body.div:
			1. ἀνεκαθήραμεν] lit. ’cleaned up’;
a ref. to the passage of Plato quoted
above p. 11.

			10. περίεστιν] ‘they still exist’;
or perhaps, ‘they have existence in
abundance’; cp. § 25.

			11. δι’ ἀέρος] sc. φέρεται. Καθ’
ὕδατος sc. ἐστίν, ’under the water’;
like κατὰ γῆς ’underground’: cp. § 24.

			12. ζωὴν δίδ] sc. to the body;
and yet it receives from the body a
share in its πάθη.
